HEADWORD: Halfness
<hw>Half"ness</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧f"n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality of being half; incompleteness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As soon as there is any departure from simplicity, and attempt at
<qex>halfness</qex>, or good for me that is not good for him, my
neighbor feels the wrong.</q> <rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halfpace</ent>⟦br⟧
